## Chapter 22 The Problem with Product Roadmaps

- The issue is that anytime you put a list of ideas on a document entitled "roadmap" no matter how many disclaimers you put on it, people across the company will interpret the items as a commitment.
- First inconvenient truth is that at least half of our product ideas are not going to work.
- Second inconvenient truth even with the ideas that do prove to be valuable, usable, feasible, and viable, it typically takes several iterations to get the execution of this idea to the point where it delivers the expected business value that management was hoping for.
